.TH "ishtp_cl_alloc_dma_buf" 9 "ishtp_cl_alloc_dma_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ishtp_cl_alloc_dma_buf \- Allocate DMA RX and TX buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ishtp_cl_alloc_dma_buf
.BI "(struct ishtp_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
ishtp device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate RX and TX DMA buffer once during bus setup.
It allocates 1MB, RX and TX DMA buffer, which are divided
into slots.
